Simply put, recycling doesn’t work.  It is estimated that only 9% of all plastic has been successfully recycled, and it's usually turned into something of lower value or “downcycled” to a point where it cannot be reused again.

Recycling is simply an excuse for the plastic industry to keep producing plastic at exponential rates, without claiming any responsibility for the true end-of-life outcomes of plastic waste.
Surfrider is proud to support vital laws and policies like the Break Free From Plastic Pollution Act, which will help stop the flow of plastic waste into our environment.

Learn more about Surfrider’s efforts to reduce plastic pollution and become part of the #BetterBeachAlliance at surfrider.org (link in our bio)

